node.text:
It's #SpotlightSaturday and this is a record setting edition! 

Bravo Zulu to eight #USCG rescue swimmers who recently earned the @guinnessworldrecords for climbing the 29,028 foot height of Mt. Everest at Air Station Cape Cod. The crew completed the climb in 1 hour, 26 minutes and 20 seconds beating the prior record held by eight Royal Air Force firefighters by 30 minutes. 

#guinessworldrecords #worldrecord #SemperParatus #USCG #GoCoastGuard #CoastGuard #military #militarycareer #careergoals #BZ #USA 🇺🇸⚓️👏

node.text: #Helicopter operations are one of the most vital parts of search and rescue (SAR) missions conducted by the #CoastGuard. node.text:
Lieutenant (Lt.) Jessica Shafer is one of only 14 women to become a Surfman in the #CoastGuard and became the first female commanding officer of Coast Guard Station Cape Disappointment in 2018, 141 years after the station first opened. Lt. Shafer is an elite lifeboat pilot, having earned coxswain, heavy weather coxswain, tactical coxswain and surfman qualifications, as well as multiple boarding officer certifications.

Lt. Shafer on why she joined the #USCG: “The benefits were unbelievable...so that was the appeal, plus the outdoors, and the physical nature of it. Seeing the country, and serving the country. Volunteerism was a big part of it also. I wanted to be in a job where people wanted to be there.” #GoCoastGuard #SemperParatus #CareerGoals #MilitaryCareer #WomensHistoryMonth #militarywomen #whyjoin #notyouraveragejob #USA 🇺🇸⚓️

node.text:
Damn, that's a lot of yayo!

While patrolling the Mona Passage waters - which connects the Atlantic Ocean to the Caribbean Sea - the crew of the #USCG Joseph Tezanos, with the assistance of a Customs and Border Protection (CBP) Air and Marine Operations (AMO) Multi-Role Enforcement Aircraft (MEA), stopped a speed boat which resulted in the apprehension of the suspected smugglers and the seizure of 1,106 lbs of cocaine worth nearly $15 million. #BravoZulu!

If you're interested in enforcing the law and the mission of the U.S. Coast Guard, send us a DM to chat with a recruiter today.

#SemperParatus #GoCoastGuard #CoastGuard #military #militarycareer #careergoals #motivation #USA 🇺🇸⚓️

Our #Coasties are Always Ready because our mission requires us to be. Air dropping emergency equipment and supplies to aid those in distress and help facilitate the rescue is just one of the many things that we do to keep mariners safe (and the view isn't too bad either).⁠
⁠
P.S.: what is your go-to move?⁠

node.text:
It's #SpotlightSaturday! #BravoZulu to U.S. Coast Guard ninjas, Lieutenant Junior Grade (LTJG) Christopher White and Petty Officer Deren Perez!

LTJG White from Sector Long Island Sound, the 2020 Coast Guard Elite Male Athlete of the year in the #USCG, is currently competing in season six of the @nationalninjaleague, placing in the top five in 11 of 13 competitions. He currently sits in first place in both the Nationwide Adult Division and New England region and is aiming to have a second appearance on the televised show American Ninja Warrior in 2021.

@guahan.ninja, the first full time recruiter stationed at U.S. Coast Guard Sector Guam, recently competed in @ninjawarrior Qualifiers Round 2 and placed 24th which was good enough to earn a spot in the semifinals! 

Cowabunga, Coastie ninjas!

#SemperParatus #motivation #USCG #GoCoastGuard #CoastGuard #military #militarycareer #careergoals #USA 🇺🇸⚓️

node.text:
No days off! ⁠
⁠
You never know what amazing things you will find if you don't take the chance to go searching for them. Even on off-days, Coasties need their exercise, especially rescue swimmers. Here, Aviation Survival Technician (AST2) Hauser free dives to 60’ and gets an amazing view doing it. ⁠
⁠
Bonus question: what kind of fish do you see?⁠
⁠
